title: Centaur issue delays JPSS-2 launch
summary: The launch of a polar-orbiting weather satellite and reentry technology demonstration will be delayed more than a week because of a battery problem with the upper stage of their rocket, NASA announced Oct. 29.

title: Psyche launch rescheduled for October 2023
summary: A NASA mission to an asteroid that missed its launch window this fall because of technical issues has been rescheduled for launch next October.

title: Constellation antenna provider SatixFy goes public after SPAC merger
summary: Satcoms equipment maker SatixFy started trading publicly Oct. 28 after its stock listing overcame waning investor interest in blank check mergers and the death of its co-founder and former CEO.

title: NASA to Provide Update on Artemis I Moon Mission
summary: NASA will host a media teleconference at 12 p.m. EDT Thursday, Nov. 3, to discuss the status of its Artemis I flight test that will launch the Space Launch System (SLS) rocket from NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The uncrewed mission will send the Orion spacecraft beyond the Moon and back to Earth before future missions with crew.

title: NASA Sets TV Coverage for Cargo Launch to International Space Station
summary: NASA and commercial cargo provider Northrop Grumman are targeting 5:50 a.m. EST, Sunday, Nov. 6, for launch of the company’s 18th resupply mission to the International Space Station.

title: NASA and ESA Agree on Next Steps to Return Mars Samples to Earth
summary: The agency’s Perseverance rover will establish the first sample depot on Mars.

title: SpaceX’s Falcon Heavy test-fired on launch pad in Florida
summary: SpaceX fired up 27 engines on a Falcon Heavy rocket Thursday night at Kennedy Space Center, sending a rumble across the spaceport in a hold-down test-firing before a launch next week for the U.S. Space Force.

title: Next Artemis 1 launch attempt on schedule for mid-November
summary: Preparations for the next attempt to launch the Space Launch System rocket on the Artemis 1 mission remain on schedule for the middle of November, but agency officials said launch opportunities may be limited if it slips to later in the month because of the Thanksgiving holiday.

title: Rocket Report: Norway’s nuclear rocket concerns; Ariane 6 delayed again
summary: "When the briefing ended, I was baffled and, if I’m honest, angry."

title: Chinese commercial remote sensing satellite firm to double size of constellation
summary: Chinese commercial firm Changguang Satellite Technology says it will expand its under-construction Jilin-1 constellation from 138 to 300 satellites.
